skills: AWS Infrastructure is looking for an experienced software engineer to lead development of the resource planning system responsible for fulfilling all demand for AWS compute and storage capacity. This capacity delivery program now lands more server capacity daily than ran the entirety of Amazon.com in the year 2004-when it was already a $7B/year business. At this scale, even small optimizations in how the system allocates power, space, network, and server inventory can have material impacts on the business's bottom line. The resource planning system must efficiently navigate this broad and deep network of interdependent fulfillment options to maximize AWS availability while minimizing cost. Succeeding in this role requires a willingness to attack hard problems and the persistence necessary to solve them, a passion for engineering excellence, and an eagerness to dive deep to become a domain expert in the data center and supply chain space. Basic Qualifications Bachelor's degree in computer science or related field 5+ years professional experience in software development Proficiency in at least one modern programming language (e.g., Java) and Unix command-line tools Preferred Qualifications Track record of technical leadership and engineering mentorship Knowledge and interest in combinatorial optimization problems and tools Practical experience with Scala, Haskell, or another functional programming language Graduate degree in computer science or related field
title: Software Development Engineer - AWS Capacity Delivery

skills: Amazon EC2 Container Service team (Amazon ECS) is looking for Software Development Engineers (SDEs) to help drive the development of new features, functionality, and capabilities. The Amazon EC2 Container Service is a newly formed team building a core set of services that allow our customers to run, manage, and deploy Docker containers at scale. Are you interested in Docker, Mesos, or API design? This team will address very unique scaling and implementation problems that directly impact how developers and organizations consume computing capacity in the cloud. You'll be part of a world-class team in a fast-paced environment that has the entrepreneurial feel of a start-up. This is an opportunity to operate and engineer systems on a massive scale, and to gain top-notch experience in cloud computing. You'll be surrounded by people who are wickedly smart, passionate about cloud computing, and believe that world-class service is critical to customer success. You will design and build the operational scalability that sustains the platform's insane growth. You will measure your success and it will be visible. The ideal candidate will be clearly passionate about the large opportunity that Amazon ECS presents and about web services in general. The ideal candidate will be passionate about the potential of cloud computing, and about building simple and elegant software solutions and customer-centric products. This person has thrived and succeeded in delivering high quality solutions in a hyper-growth environment where priorities shift fast. If you're looking to solve challenging technical problems and create great products for customers, then this is the right role for you! To learn more about Amazon EC2 Container Service: https://aws.amazon.com/ecs
